Williamson, Mark wrote:

&gt;Hi,
&gt;
&gt;Last night I was doing a broad ranging crawl from 
&gt;(www.yahoo.com , path depth 3, disk included frontier 
&gt;and broadscope, slightly more agressive than default)
&gt;and this morning it had -1 of 50 active threads. The log 
&gt;files where full of too many files open errors. I had 
&gt;hit about 12000 unique domains ( I was gathering URLS to
&gt;test a consistent hash algorithm). 
&gt;
&gt;I seem to be able to reproduce this consistently - is this 
&gt;a know bug or is there a setting I can change to help it?
&gt;
&gt;cheers 
&gt;  
&gt;
Heyup Mark.

On the too many open files, checkout the FAQ.  You&#39;ll have to boost your 
limit if you&#39;re doing broad crawls:  
http://crawler.archive.org/faq.html#toomanyopenfiles.  You might want to 
also check the Known Limitations doc. if you haven&#39;t already since 
you&#39;re trying broad crawls:  
http://crawler.archive.org/articles/limitations.html.

Hope that helps some.
Good on you  Mark,
St.Ack

